body:
_What are the reasons/motivation for this change?_

Fix #5465.

```
[read_verilog -sv|verific -sv|read_slang] << EOF
module set_param #(
    parameter logic [3:0] VALUE
) (
    output logic [3:0] out
);
    assign out = VALUE;
endmodule

module top (
);
    localparam [3:0] a = '1;
    wire [3:0] b;
    wire [3:0] c = '1;
    set_param #('1) sp (b);
    always @* begin
        assert(a == 4'b1111);
        assert(b == 4'b1111);
        assert(c == 4'b1111);
    end
endmodule
EOF
prep -top top -flatten
chformal -lower
select top
sat -prove-asserts -verify -show-all
```

Running the above script (with main) with `read_verilog` only passes the assertion on `c`, while both `verific` and `read_slang` pass all three.

_Explain how this is achieved._

For the `localparam [3:0] a = '1;` case we check the `is_unsized` field, using the same logic as the `AST_CASE_SIZE`: https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys/blob/5d0847f6fbef980914134a6a98b2397ecb0a3189/frontends/ast/simplify.cc#L4394-L4403

`set_param #('1) sp (b);` is a bit more difficult, requiring a new `CONST_FLAG_UNSIZED` to preserve the `is_unsized` field from the AST in the `RTLIL::Const` struct.

_Make sure your change comes with tests. If not possible, share how a reviewer might evaluate it._

Tests included and run by CI.

